##Online consultation: The "Second Front" in the fight against the epidemic

Micro-signal. NBWEEKLY

Introduction of function, new media with temperature

The on-line consultation mainly aims at the mild disease patient to carry on the illness preliminary judgment and provides the suggestion, to the serious disease patient or the suggestion goes to the off-line outpatient service doctor.

By Ding Ning

Zhang Ning, 21, who had been coughing at home for half a month, walked to the fever clinic and returned home for fear of cross infection. While fidgeting, Zhang Ning found a link to the micro-medical online consultation that had been reposted on her friends'network. As a test, Zhang Ning sent his symptoms online to doctors: "Cough at night, no fever, no travel history in Wuhan, no exposure to pneumonia patients. " Ten minutes later, zhang Ning got the doctor's advice to stay home. Before that, she had never used the "online consultation" function. Zhang Ning told Nandu weekly that she wakes up every morning to see the increase in the number of confirmed cases in the news and wonders if she might be at risk.

Li, who returned home from school in Wuhan, had similar anxieties. Li said he had been home for more than 10 days, during which he appeared to have a slight cold and fever, but only 37.3 degrees, and no symptoms of cough. Keeping a thermometer in hand, afraid to talk too much with his family, day to day to consider whether to go to the hospital, has become a daily portrayal of Li Xiang. Only yesterday, online breathing doctor told Li Xiang "advised to stay at home, do not fear, according to the symptoms of isolation at home on the line, " he was slightly relieved.

Figure shows a screenshot of the online interview provided by the interviewee

As the number of people diagnosed with COVID-19 pneumonia has soared, many are caught in the dilemma of whether to go to the hospital or observe at home. "on-line consultation" has become the second way for many people to seek medical treatment.

How reliable is "online consultation" ? What are the formal platforms available? How should it be used properly?

Online consultation is a hot topic

Pop Up message box, ask about the condition, reply to the patient... on New Year's Eve, Sichuan People's Hospital, Zhang Yan is the attending physician in the Department of Respiratory Medicine to guard the mobile phone. In recent days, Zhang Yan has been on the Internet nonstop Free Clinic, as of Jan. 27, has seen nearly 800 patients.

Just finished a day of offline outpatient clinic, 27 pm, Shenzhen Children's Hospital, director of respiratory medicine picked up the phone, began online to respond to patients. "The parents who were consulted were very anxious and under a lot of psychological pressure, and I always answered their questions in my spare time, " Xu said.

Like Zhang Yan and COVID-19, he had seen more than 10,000 doctors online during the pneumonia outbreak. As of 10:00 am on January 28, the "peace and good doctor" had received 948,000 consultations related to the epidemic; as of 9:00 am on January 29, there were 12,775 nominal doctors on the "micro-doctor" platform, providing a total of about 620,000 consultations, the platform has been visited 70 million times. At the bottom of the platform's interface, doctors from all over the country can be seen "continuing to provide assistance" almost every minute. On several online medical platforms, the number of patients from Hubei Province continued to flood in, Caixin reported, up to 3,000 passengers per hour.

"medical resources are tight everywhere, especially in Wuhan, and online consultation is a very important auxiliary battlefield in this epidemic, " Chen Xiangjun, director of the Otolaryngology at Southern Medical University, said in an interview.

The picture shows that the doctor is conducting an on-line consultation

What is "on-line consultation" ?

"on-line consultation" originates from "mobile medical" under the background of Internet, also called "non-contact medical" , which corresponds to "contact" between doctors and patients in traditional medical way. "online consultation" in the two sides do not need to meet, through text, pictures, voice and other means, on the Internet platform for non-contact Information Exchange.

At present, due to the excessive number of people seeking medical treatment in some areas, medical resources are under pressure, wuhan Union Hospital, Wuhan Tongji Hospital, Wuxi Third People's Hospital, Sichuan Provincial People's Hospital and other online infection of the COVID-19 pneumonia to open "fever clinic" consultation channels. "Ali Health" , "Dr. Syzygium Aromaticum" , "Ping an good doctor" , "good doctor" , "micro-doctor" , tencent wechat and other platforms also provide relevant "online consultation" services.

According to the "measures for the administration of Internet diagnosis and treatment" promulgated by the National Health Commission in 2018, medical institutions shall not carry out Internet diagnosis and treatment activities for first-time patients. As a result, most of the current online medical platforms offer only light consultations, offering advice rather than diagnosis and prescriptions.

The picture shows the "online consultation" platform of the "micro-medical" and "Ping an good doctor" apps

How to use "on-line consultation" ?

Before using "on-line Outpatient Service" , must first have the foundation to the condition judgment.

According to the first study of 41 patients published in the Lancet on January 24, pneumonia patients with COVID-19 infection had fever (98% , 40 cases) , cough (76% , 31 cases) and fatigue (44% , 18 cases) . More than half of the patients also presented with dyspnea (55% , 22 cases) , but headache (8% , 3 cases) and diarrhea (3% , 1 case) were rare.

In an interview with southern metropolis weekly, Zhang Yan said, as long as the patient does not have an epidemiological history (i.e. a history of epidemiological exposure, which at this stage means a history of travel to Hubei within two weeks of the onset of symptoms such as cough and fever, especially in Wuhan, or a history of contact with a patient with fever in Hubei) , fever, cough or other serious symptoms such as dyspnea, it is suggested to rest at home after online consultation and monitor your body temperature from time to time.

According to the Xi'an Evening News, an expert in Infectious Diseases at the second affiliated Hospital of Xi'an Jiaotong University said: Winter and spring are already high respiratory disease seasons, sneezing and SNIFFLING, common symptoms of everyday illness, are not common symptoms of COVID-19 pneumonia. If there is no Wuhan contact history, more likely to be the common cold, influenza, bronchitis and so on. Therefore, there is no need to cluster fever clinics for minor discomfort, which can lead to cross-infection and place an additional burden on limited medical resources.

If the child has a fever for one to two days, but the temperature is not very high (below 38.5 degrees) , he can drink more water and eat a balanced diet at home, Xu Jianqiang, director of Shenzhen Children's Hospital, told Nandu weekly, eat more fruits and vegetables that contain vitamin C. But if the fever for a long time or high fever or accompanied by a headache, fatigue, poor mental symptoms, parents should take their children to the hospital.

After completing the basic judgment, where to look for the regular platform? At present, in addition to the public number of some hospitals to open an online consultation platform, there are also some medical platforms also set up a "online consultation" zone. Take Tongji Hospital as an example, you can download "Palmtop Tongji" APP and find "online consultation-fever clinic" for online consultation after registration.

On January 25, tencent Wechat also launched "City service-fever clinic" and wechat search "online consultation" to provide online consultation services for patients. As of January 28, more than a dozen public hospitals, including the Wuhan Union Hospital, the Third People's Hospital of Mianyang, the First People's Hospital of Shaoguan, the Guangzhou University of Chinese Medicine Jinshazhou Hospital, the Seventh Affiliated Hospital of the National Sun Yat-sen University, and the Third Affiliated Hospital of the Southern Medical University, have voluntarily set up special online consultation areas. The Wuhan Union Hospital put 320 doctors on a 24 hour rotation and saw 12,000 patients a day. More than 200 doctors have been admitted to Yichang's Central People's hospital, and more than 4,000 citizens have been consulted in the four to five hours since the online consultation was launched.

In addition, in the alipay interface search "ask experts" can also find the COVID-19 infection of pneumonia consultation zone.

The picture shows the online consultation of the payment interface

"Due to the special nature of this epidemic, the Internet is not limited by factors such as location and time, and psychological relief for this epidemic can also be carried out in a large area through the Internet, " said Dr. Wenzhou Medical College, a member of the national expert group on Psychological Crisis Intervention and director of the Department of Psychiatry at the Kangning hospital affiliated to the National Psychological Crisis Intervention Center, due to the limitations of online consultation in terms of communication channels, total amount of information, depth of communication and accuracy of information, Tang Wei, director of the Wenzhou Medical College, said in an interview, medical workers are always crossing the river by feeling the stones.

"online consultations can reduce the risk of cross-infection to some extent, but things like throat conditions, lung auscultation, routine blood tests, viral nucleic acid screening, and so on, can not be done online, " Zhang Yan said, the on-line consultation mainly aims at the mild disease patient to carry on the illness preliminary judgment and provides the suggestion, to the serious disease patient or the suggestion goes to the off-line outpatient service doctor.

Is "on-line consultation" standard?

Are All online consultants licensed to practice medicine? How do you ensure that your doctor's information is reliable? Zhou Yu, the head of Wechat, said in an interview that the wechat platforms are all officially run by public hospitals and doctors are all licensed doctors in their hospitals. "micro-doctors" told southern weekly that doctors involved in the fight against COVID-19 pneumonia can sign up online and submit medical ID card, license, professional title card and other license information. In the authentication phase, the "micro-doctor" will be the applicant for the portrait of the Living Body Test, will be compared with the photo on the identity card, to ensure that the applicant is operating.

But during the interview, patients reported that non-smoking doctors also answered questions online about the symptoms of pneumonia. Some platforms are early AI triage, the response speed is very fast, but the machine set the fixed answer occasionally answer the phenomenon of not asked.

Figure provides the profile of the new coronavirus on-line outpatient clinic for the respondents

In response, the Wuhan Union Hospital said in an interview, at present, the hospital quickly developed the epidemic screening, treatment and prevention rules, medical staff after basic training for online services. Southern Medical University, Director of the Otolaryngology at Shenzhen Hospital, told southern metropolis weekly that doctors who participate in online consultations with "micro-doctors" set up a wechat group, where doctors discuss with each other questions they are unsure about. "Safe Doctor" online consultation adopts "AI + real person" mode, the front end is intelligent consultation in response, and then according to the specific description of the illness to the doctor to solve.

In addition to physical therapy, the "micro-medical" platform also offers online psychological assistance. He said the psychological problems caused by COVID-19's pneumonia could not be ignored. At present, patients receiving medical treatment can be divided into two types of personnel within and outside Hubei Province from a geographical perspective, from the physical health status can be divided into non-isolated status, the family in isolation and their own non-isolation, they are being isolated and they have been diagnosed, and other different groups. The symptoms are also divided into anxiety, panic attacks, somatization disorders, depression, sleep disorders, obsessive-compulsive disorder, stress disorders and other different symptoms.

"online psychological assistance can not tell patients' facial expressions, movements, body language and the safety of their environment. Proper language communication becomes very important. How to start and end a topic online is a great test for health care workers. On-line psychologist should also have medical, psychological background and psychological crisis intervention experience. Some patients need to be referred to offline hospitals, but we can't get in touch with them now, and it would be better if we could have accurate online and offline docking,"Tang said.

The picture shows Tang Wei who is carrying out on-line psychological rescue

Chen Xiangjun, a native of Hubei Province, is also receiving medical treatment online in Shenzhen. Seventeen years ago, he fought the SARS epidemic on the front lines of Shiyan in Hubei Province. In the course of the interview, he mentioned that more than 100 of his classmates were "struggling" at Tongji and Xiehe Hospitals in Wuhan. He choked up several times, "The first doctor to die in Wuhan was one of our Otolaryngology. I was ready to go to the front in the second battlefield. "

(Zhang Ning and Shang appear as pseudonyms.)

Source | NANDU weekly

The symptoms are also divided into anxiety, panic attacks, somatization disorders, depression, sleep disorders, obsessive-compulsive disorder, stress disorders and other different symptoms.

"online psychological assistance can not tell patients' facial expressions, movements, body language and the safety of their environment. Proper language communication becomes very important. How to start and end a topic online is a great test for health care workers. On-line psychologist should also have medical, psychological background and psychological crisis intervention experience. Some patients need to be referred to offline hospitals, but we can't get in touch with them now, and it would be better if we could have accurate online and offline docking,"Tang said.

In response, the Wuhan Union Hospital said in an interview, at present, the hospital quickly developed the epidemic screening, treatment and prevention rules, medical staff after basic training for online services. Southern Medical University, Director of the Otolaryngology at Shenzhen Hospital, told southern metropolis weekly that doctors who participate in online consultations with "micro-doctors" set up a wechat group, where doctors discuss with each other questions they are unsure about. "Safe Doctor" online consultation adopts "AI + real person" mode, the front end is intelligent consultation in response, and then according to the specific description of the illness to the doctor to solve.

The picture shows Tang Wei who is carrying out on-line psychological rescue

Chen Xiangjun, a native of Hubei Province, is also receiving medical treatment online in Shenzhen. Seventeen years ago, he fought the SARS epidemic on the front lines of Shiyan in Hubei Province. In the course of the interview, he mentioned that more than 100 of his classmates were "struggling" at Tongji and Xiehe Hospitals in Wuhan. He choked up several times, "The first doctor to die in Wuhan was one of our Otolaryngology. I was ready to go to the front in the second battlefield. "
